according to avida cbd, their goal is ‚Äúto help as many people lead a healthier more active lifestyle in an all organic and ethical way.‚Äù they operate under 3 core principles to achieve this- let the customer know exactly what they are getting, only offer the best cbd products at affordable prices, and offer a 5-star customer experience. in this video, we‚Äôll be taking a look at the avida cbd vape oil range and seeing if they‚Äôve managed to achieve this.

the pipette has a thin spout, which makes it suitable for a lot of different cartridge types when it‚Äôs time to refill. avida cbd has formulated their juice to be atomized at any wattage, so you don‚Äôt need to remember a particular setting. a 1-3 second pull is enough to create a decent cloud, and the flavor hits you from the first second.

avida cbd vape juice comes in four flavors, manga mango, berry grape, blue razz, and flavorless additive. flavorless additive may not sound the most exciting, but it‚Äôs good to see avida cbd have all bases covered. our favorite is the manga mango- it‚Äôs light, fragrant and doesn‚Äôt come with that slightly burnt aftertaste that affects some juices. as with a lot of high-quality juices, the cbd taste still blends well at higher strengths as well. each flavor was developed by avida‚Äôs own in-house award-winning flavorist, and you definitely taste that extra love and attention.

Video_Title: TIMELAPSE OF THE FUTURE: A Journey to the End of Time (4K)
Description:
support my work on patreon: https://www.patreon.com/melodysheep  |  get the soundtrack: https://bit.ly/2hkl9fi  |   how's it all gonna end?  this experience takes us on a journey to the end of time, trillions of years into the future, to discover what the fate of our planet and our universe may ultimately be. 

we start in 2019 and travel exponentially through time, witnessing the future of earth, the death of the sun, the end of all stars, proton decay, zombie galaxies, possible future civilizations, exploding black holes, the effects of dark energy, alternate universes, the final fate of the cosmos - to name a few.

this is a picture of the future as painted by modern science - a picture that will surely evolve over time as we dig for more clues to how our story will unfold. much of the science is very recent - and new puzzle pieces are still waiting to be found.

to me, this overhead view of time gives a profound perspective - that we are living inside the hot flash of the big bang, the perfect moment to soak in the sights and sounds of a universe in its glory days, before it all fades away.  although the end will eventually come, we have a practical infinity of time to play with if we play our cards right. the future may look bleak, but we have enormous potential as a species. 

featuring the voices of david attenborough, craig childs, brian cox, neil degrasse tyson, michelle thaller, lawrence krauss, michio kaku, mike rowe, phil plait, janna levin, stephen hawking, sean carroll, alex filippenko, and martin rees.
